s derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert At-Sea was born about 1470, in Herne, Kent, England. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Millicent. He died in 1544, in his hometown, at the age of 75."},"et":{"about 1470–1544":"umbes 1470–1544","–Female":"Surnud","1525–1553":"1525–1553","1495–1537":"1495–1537","1500–1543":"1500–1543","1470–1544":"1470–1544","1525":"1525","about 1470":"umbes 1470","1544":"1544","1500":"1500","1543":"1543","1553":"1553","10 July 1537":"10. juuli 1537","1495":"1495","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1470":"1470","about 1495":"umbes 1495","1537":"1537","Kent, England":"Kent, England","London, England":"London, England","Herne, Kent, England":"Herne, Kent, England"},"fi":{"about 1470–1544":"noin 1470–1544","–Female":"Kuollut","1525–1553":"1525–1553","1495–1537":"1495–1537","1500–1543":"1500–1543","1470–1544":"1470–1544","1525":"1525","about 1470":"noin 1470","1544":"1544","1500":"1500","1543":"1543","1553":"1553","10 July 1537":"10. heinäkuuta 1537","1495":"1495","about 1500":"noin 1500","1470":"1470","about 1495":"noin 1495","1537":"1537","Kent, England":"Kent, England","London, England":"London, England","Herne, Kent, England":"Herne, Kent, England"},"fr":{"about 1470–1544":"environ 1470–1544","–Female":"Décédée","1525–1553":"1525–1553","1495–1537":"1495